## ICIJ Offshore Leaks Database

**Provider:** International Consortium of Investigative Journalists (ICIJ)
**Datasets:** Panama Papers, Paradise Papers, Pandora Papers, and others
**Portal:** https://offshoreleaks.icij.org/
**Download:** https://offshoreleaks-data.icij.org/offshoreleaks/csv/full-oldb.LATEST.zip

### License

The ICIJ Offshore Leaks Database is dual-licensed:

| Component          | License                                      | URL                                                        |
|--------------------|----------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
| Database structure | Open Database License (ODbL) v1.0            | https://opendatacommons.org/licenses/odbl/1-0/             |
| Database contents  | Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0  | https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/            |

Both licences **allow commercial use** and both **require attribution**.

### Required Attribution

All interfaces (UI and API) that surface ICIJ data must display or return:

> Includes data from the ICIJ Offshore Leaks Database, licensed under
> ODbL v1.0 (database structure) and CC BY-SA 3.0 (contents).
> © International Consortium of Investigative Journalists.
> https://offshoreleaks.icij.org/

### Implementation Notes

- **Frontend:** `DataSourcesFooter` component in `frontend/src/components/shared/DataSourcesFooter.tsx`
- **API responses:** `attribution`, `license`, and `source_url` fields are included in all
  API responses that return ICIJ-sourced documents or entities.
- **Source module:** `periphery/ingest/sources/icij_offshore.py` — license obligations
  documented in the module docstring.
- **ODbL carve-out:** Serving query results through a web interface does **not** constitute
  "conveying" the database under ODbL §4.6. Our SaaS delivery model is compliant so long
  as attribution is displayed and included in API responses.

